In article <102102@cup.portal.com> Michael_A_Radanovich@cup.portal.com writes:
>>I can do something like toggling a bit on the parallel port with
>>each nuclear event.  What I do after that is a mystery.  Anyone
>>interested in collaborating on this?
>
>>John
>
>     I remember reading somewhere that the paralell port on some
>PC's is simply a 74374 style latch and cannot take input.  Most
>newer PC's probably have the parallel port integrated into one
>of the three or four VLSI chips that make up a whole motherboard
>these days, though, and those parallel ports should be 
>bi-directional.

Standard parallel ports have 8 output data lines (plus strobe)
but they also do have some input lines (printer ready, out
of paper, and that kind of thing).  This is how parallel port
CD-roms and similar devices work.  Using the parallel port
is a good approach for this kind of thing.
